values:
Right, so I finished my Fafsa today, I'm calling U of L (hell) tomorrow and finishing up the money I owe them in a payment plan... I cannot WAIT!  I'm so excited to announce the news...  I'M GOING BACK TO COLLEGE!

I'm so hyped, I think I wanna take a communications class, math class (rudimentary of course since I've been out of college almost 2 years), and definitely my clarinet lessons... OH!  And I've always wanted to take an art class!  YAY!

So EXCITED!

as far enough to say...


LOL This excited...
>_<  adorable isn't he?  Not as "hot" as a phoenix, but he'll definitely do.



Anyway... So, college choices are as follows:
1. Morehead State University
2. Indiana University-Southeast
3. Eastern Kentucky University

I don't really care which one... I'm definitely willing to pick any of them at this point in time, although if I could go back to Morehead I would most definitely have the joy of being with all my old friends!  :D 

I'm happy to be back to my old self, and I can see how happy I am and I'm relieved...  I never thought I'd get to go back to be the happy person I once was long ago.  W00T for Renaissance and W00T for college!?!?

or as my colleagues spell it..  c0//3g3 ... well whatever the lingo I'm SUPER STOKED!

My first entry...  well I'd just like to say that I am quite excited to be back to LJ, missed it a bit.  I shall be adding people at random to be my friends; however, if you run across my journal and you'd like to be apart of my friends list, please don't hesitate to write a comment on this entry!  Thanks!!

BTW!  Everyone, you can call me... Fennik!
